    <h2>
      <a href="/episodes/9-filtering-sensitive-logs">Filtering Sensitive Logs</a>
      
    </h2>
    <div class="description">
      Are you accepting sensitive user data? Passwords, credit card numbers, etc. By default, Rails stores all submitted parameters in plain text in the logs. This episode will show you how to filter this sensitive input so it doesn&#x27;t show up in the log file.
      <span class="stats">(2 minutes)</span>
    </div>
    <div class="watch">
        <a href="/episodes/9-filtering-sensitive-logs?autoplay=true" class="pretty_button">Watch Episode</a>
